Nov 19 2009 	Great Price for a NICE place so close to the strip! Very un-Vegas...	Our business event was at a hotel/casino straight down on the strip, the white original nice one on the corner... We have stayed there, but I never felt I got my money's worth for what they charge. Tuscany Suites, however, was the opposite! Can't BELIEVE what we got for under $100 total per night! Additionally, we received a coupon book that made it an even better deal for dining, drinks, and gambling. A total steal.EVERYONE who works there that we interacted with at this place was genuinely nice, even the phone operators; they were all REAL people and seemed to like their jobs. Employees consistently went beyond what was required - reservations, front desk, etc. The room, well it's what everyone else describes. HUGE! It would make a GREAT studio apartment. We kept our snacks and drinks in the fridge. You can request a microwave if you want one. There's a table and chairs, PLUS a &quot;living room area,&quot; PLUS a desk, then the bed was waaaay over on the other side. The bathroom had a separate shower and bath, huge.The restaurants, bars, and casino were all very nice. I noticed it's NOT full of &quot;creepy people.&quot; The people who choose this place are a mix, but normal people, various ages, smart enough to not pay 3 times as much less than a mile away on the strip, apparently. Even the gift shop was full of surprisingly nice items, not just the usual Vegas tourist crap.We didn't go to the live music club and dancing, but we were around it for a bit, and again, nice, normal people, decent drink prices, good cover band. Dana, the manager of the Italian restaurant Tuscany Gardens, was great. She left me her cell number to accommodate the large party I wanted to book. The prices there were VERY good, as if were were in a normal town. By pricing, you would never know you were near the strip! The service was truly great as well, they handled our big party wonderfully. Dinner entrees were only $13-$15 for most listed. Everyone in our party of 20 was quite pleased with price and quality, and it's a pretty restaurant.I feel like we discovered a hidden gem right off the strip. It's not just a great price, it's also NICE.	
