Nov 16 2009 	We would definately go back there	Great weekend price and a HUGE well maintained room. Fridge, sink, sofa bed, separate shower, tub and toilet in its own room make this perfect for families or even couples. Parking is a breeze, food in all of the resturants was above average and well priced. Casino was well laid out and very clean. All of the employees we encountered were polite and knowlegable. The walk to the Strip was not very long, but a bit perilous due to construction and a seedy bunch of locals. This is not unusual for off strip locals, and that is too bad. There are a lot of nice places to visit and eat within a few blocks of the strip. Vegas needs to improve the look and the safety of ALL the streets adjacent to the strip. Side walks, crosswalks and street lighting are a joke for a city this size and with that much tax revenue, but I think the big hotels fight this to keep people from wandering away and not spending every dime in their rip-off super hotels, home of the $13.00 hamburger.	
