Nov 11 2009 	New spacious gracious and QUIET	This hotel is absolutely the best of both worlds. It's a block and a half from the strip on E. Flamingo, but an entire world away from the craziness. We paid $79 for a Saturday night and only $35 (!!!) for the Sunday night after fleeing from our pre-paid pigstye at the Imperial Dump (aka the Imperial Palace). Our SUITE at Tuscany was easily 3 times the size of the room at the Imperial Dump. It was huge, NEW, and blissfully quiet. The beds were luxury-hotel style and sheer heaven after the lumps of rocks that pass for beds at the Imperial Dump. We ate at Marilyn's at Tuscany - the food was excellent, nearly HALF the price of the Imperial Dump, and the service was fantastic. From the ladies at the front desk, to the concierge and everyone in between, the service at Tuscany was top notch. Even better, you didn't have to compete with cigarette-toking, half-drunk partygoers to get to where you wanted to go in the hotel. They have a great casino which hops at night, but the smoke-free guest rooms are situated well away from the noise. This hotel is walking distance (or a short cab ride) away from all the action, but heaven to come back to at night. Oh, and parking is easy, free and directly in front of the hotel (no walking miles to get your car or using a valet, although a valet is readily available at Tuscany). They also have free wi-fi, excellent conference and banquet facilities, as well as an absolutely beautiful wedding chapel. We paritcularly enjoyed the oasis of the centre-court garden and swimming pool - we felt like we'd arrived at some Caribbean resort, not a hotel in the middle of Vegas. We have made this hotel our absolute number one pick for the next time we're in LV.	
