Oct 9 2009 	A lot to like.	We stayed 4 nights at the Tuscany Suites and the place has a lot going for it particularly if you are looking for a good value and want to be close to the Strip (without having to put up with the nonstop frenetic craziness).As others have said, the rooms are huge with a separate kitchen area and bathrooms with a separate water closet. The furnishings are functional and nothing fancy. My wife described them as &quot;something you might find in a cottage.&quot; The TV was a standard screen with limited channels, but did you really come to Las Vegas to watch TV? My biggest room surprise was that this is the only Vegas hotel I've ever been in where you could open the windows all the way! Since it was in the low to mid 70's we kept the windows open the whole time we were there and didn't have to fuss with the AC. We had a king bed that was firm and comfortable.Unlike the high rise towers that dominate Vegas, Tuscany is made up of a compound of 16 three story buildings. The curvy pathways between are nicely landscaped so it's even fun to walk to the pool, casino, fitness center, etc. It's so peaceful that you could forget you're in Las Vegas until you look up and see the Strip hotels towering over you. Speaking of pools, there are two. The main one is a free form with a large jacuzzi. The second is a lap pool also with a jacuzzi. Both were very well maintained. In most other locations this property would likely be considered a 3-1/2 star place. Becuase it has to compete with likes of Wynn, Venetian, Mandalay Bay et al. it's tough to get that kind of rating.The casino is small and comfortably quiet. It had all the usual slots and table games. Drink service was very good and most of the staff was friendly. The one exception was the bartender who worked during the Monday Night Football party. He seemed to cater to his friends and ignore the rest of the bar. We didn't bother going to the lounge after that.We ate at the 24 hour coffe shop (Marilyn's Cafe) twice and the Mexican restaurant (Cantina) once. The staff was extremely pleasant and went out of their way to make sure everything was okay. The food was very good in both. There is also an upscale Italian restaurant which we didn't try.On check in we recieved a coupon book for BOGO at the restaurants along with a slot card incentive, free drink coupons and a few other goodies. Considering the extremely reasonble price of the rooms, the couplon book turned a good value into a great value.The Good: great location - 2 blocks from the strip Windows that open all the way Good water pressure in shower Pretty in a peaceful way. Free internet in the common areas. Mostly friendly staffThe Not So Good - Our room in Building L overlooked a vacant lot.. Ambient noise from the street. (but I guess that's the . price you pay for leaving the windows open.) Charge for internet in the room.None of these were major issues, and the hotel had no control over the first two. We would (and probably will) stay here again.	
