Sep 12 2009 	Reasonable Rates But Lacking Previous Luster	Spent a nite at the Tuscany on Sun of Labor Day weekend since the rate was much better than we could get on the strip. We've been there before but this time we thought the rooms were showing their age. They are very large with a kitchenette and huge bathroom but our carpet was frayed and not as clean as we would have liked. When we tried to check in at 2:00 (check-in is advertised as 3:00) we were told that we could have an early check-in for $12 extra. We said we would wait. The woman at the front desk said she would take care of all of the paperwork since we were there but we had to come back at 3:00 to pick up our key which didn't seem to make much sense but then neither did the early check-in fee. We also had to pay an additional $10 &quot;resort fee&quot; when we checked out - we were told it was for the use of the pool, fitness center, etc, none of which we used. Can't figure out why that wasn't just included in the price of the room since it didn't appear to be optional. The hotel is located a couple blocks off the strip. Parking is free and convenient if you have a car. It's not a bad walk during the day but wouldn't have wanted to walk it without my husband in the evening. One very bright spot at the Tuscany is the Tuscan Garden Restaurant. They have very good and reasonably price Italian food. We've eaten there even when we aren't staying in the hotel and have always been pleased. As a hotel guest, we got a coupon for $20 off a bill of $40 or more in the restaurant which we were happy to use. All in all, the Tuscany is not a bad place to stay if you're looking for an inexpensive hotel, want a kitchenette, and don't mind being off the strip.	
