Aug 4 2009	Great Location for a Basketball Team	We recently took a high school level basketball team to Vegas for a national tournament. Our critieria on a hotel was off-the-strip but accessible, relatively inexpensive, nowhere near the &quot;seedy&quot; part of Vegas, reasonably nice rooms, and a decent pool. Tuscany fit the bill very well. The price was excellent...$21 on weekdays and $50 for the weekend. We were pleasantly surprised how large the rooms and bathrooms were. When you've got 4 boys sleeping in a room, it's nice to have a large bathroom and a toliet behind a separate door. There was a stove top and cooler in each room but no microwave. And there was living space to spread out. Upon check-in we received coupon books. One of the coupons, a buy-one get-one free entree at the restaurant, proved valuable to us. The restaurants are average quality but run daily specials which make them a relatively good value. Our bottom-line...they say you get what you pay for...we received much more than that.	
