Jun 25 2009 	Simple big cheap relaxing	I enjoyed my stay at Tuscany from the fast check-in to the huge standard room to the pretty pool and affordable restaurants inside the casino. The walk to the strip takes about 12 - 15 minutes depending on your speed. This was fine for us as that intersection has so much going on anyway. The room was even larger than our room at the Trump (we splurged later). It was about half price compared to anything else and everything worked great - minimal noise, got a microwave, no smoke smell, room service on request, etc. Another bonus - the cabbies know the hotel because it is so big (I was surprised) even though it's not on the strip. We ate at Marilyn's (good breakfast!) and the Cantina (not that great). A few too many kids at the pool, but the music was mellow and relaxing and there is even affordable drink service! Enjoy!!	
