May 3 2009 	Location and Price makes the Tuscany a good value! A good way to not get burnt out on Vegas!	I have stayed at the Tuscany on several different occassions for Conferences and for Family Reunions and I chose it because we decided to get married at the Flamingo and have our dinner at Bouchon (Venetian) as well as seeing Phantom of the Opera--and I the Flamingo charges an insane deposit for rooms and the Venetian was way overpriced for our group. The Tuscany had the location and the incredible prices so we all stayed there!The Tuscany is down the street from the Flamingo/Ballys-a quick ten minute walk to all of the action. This three story hotel comprises of a dozen buildings surrounding the main building. The main building includes a small casino-where the slots seem to be pretty loose-An upscale Italian restaurant, a Mexican Restaurant, a 24 restaurant, a Bar inside of the Casino, a coffee shop, a gift shop and a Lobby bar and Front Desk/Concierge. Upstairs are the conference rooms. We have stayed at this hotel before and prerequested that everyone stay in the same building-and they were able to accomodate us with that. The front lobby staff was great. We had used online websites for the best deals and that was great. I have stayed there in the past and at other hotels around the world, and the less complicated you make it, the less errors there will be. If I am splitting a room with someone I pay for it and they pay for the car or something else. (Just a traveldeva tip!) The spacious rooms have either a King or two double beds, a smallish tv on top of a dresser, a round table and four chairs, fridge and microwave and couch/Chair with table. These rooms are perfect for gathering everyone together, having a late night snack or waiting for everyone to get together. The rooms are clean, have windows that can open, have a Tuscan &quot;theme&quot; with the watercolors on the wall and the bedspread, and pale furniture. The bathroom has a shower (yes it is low, European style) as well as separate tub and toilet with a separate door. These rooms are more than functional and although not as luxurious as some hotels, this would be a Superior First class room in NYC! I would equate the rooms to be like a Country Inns and Suites or a Holiday Inn or better quality Best Western. What I love about this hotel is the ease from going from your room to the car-maybe three minutes, versus other hotels on the strip, which take a good ten minutes to get to the car park and then maneuver around the ramp to get out to the street. This is very convenient. We never ate at the Mexican or Italian restaurant, but we did eat at the 24 hour cafe, which features really reasonable prices and good solid food. This is not like eating at Mario Batali's restaurant, but the food is good and the price is great. (I am trying to set up expectations here! :)) Breakfast was tasty and one night, my brother got a chicken sandwich and he said it was tasty. The pool is not huge by any standards, but it is a pleasant pool area and we loved the coziness of it all. I never felt unsafe there, but like anywhere, in the evening, always walk outside with someone else. I did notice across the street, some homeless guys walking around. Traveling can provide false security and it is a good idea to not walk alone at night. As we had stayed in Vegas for a week, which is unusual and frankly too long, but necessary in our case, I liked that the Tuscany is away from the total Vegas insantity. When we wanted to be part of that..we headed out to the strip, but at the end of the day, it was nice to be back at our quiet, relaxing hotel.	
