Apr 29 2009	Mixed Feelings	My review will center around our stay in a Tuscany 2-bedroom suite and the service at our daughter's wedding ceremony/reception at the facility.First let me say that I had nothing to do with the planning of my daughter's nuptuals. She dealt with the Tuscany herself and had nothing but praise for the woman who handled everything for the ceremony and reception. Things could not have gone smoother or less painfully. I am very grateful for that.CHECK-IN - My husband and I were sharing the suite, and bill, with my (other) daughter and her husband and the confusion that occurred during our check-in would have been comical had it not been so upsetting. The woman that we were dealing with treated us like children and made us feel like fools. She kept saying things like &quot;this is the way it's done in Las Vegas&quot;. My daughter has traveled all over the world, including many trips to LV, and has NEVER experienced any problem like this. The woman kept trying to &quot;explain things&quot; and telling us that everything would be OK (it was not -- our Master Card bill came through totally screwed up). I spoke with other friends that weekend who had the same sort of experience at check in. Extremely frustrating. Other friends were fine. It seemed to be hit and miss.SUITE - The suite itself was OK. It was a bit tired and dark but seemed clean, spacious and functional. As mentioned in other reviews, there are no utensils of any kind in the kitchen, so it is fairly limited unless you buy paper/plastic goods, which, as an environmentalist, I am not anxious to do. The hotel would not even provide us with wine/champagne glasses to have on hand for the numerous guests that dropped by throughout our stay. Now why couldn't a hotel fill that request, especially in a suite? I thought that was sort of strange. BEDROOMS (2) - While each bedroom had a hang-up closet and bathroom, there were no dressers and therefore no drawers of any kind (except the tiny one in each bedside table). That meant that we had no choice but to leave many of our things in our suitcase which, of course, we did not rezip all the time. This was especially weird since guests had to go through the bedroom to use the bathroom, so all our &quot;stuff&quot; was pretty much out in view in the bedroom and bathroom for all to see. Again, sort of odd. (I noticed that the regular rooms all had dressers.) On the plus side, each bedroom had a flat screen wall TV in addition to the regular TV in the living room.A couple of relatively minor things: - The showerhead was mounted really low -- I'm 5'4&quot; and it was none too high for ME. Also the pressure was PAINFULLY strong and there didn't seem to be any way to soften it up, so matter how we tried.- There was no full-length mirror anywhere.- Though the bathroom was very large, there was only one, relatively useless hook (everything slid off). They could easily put several (better) hooks on the back of the door.- There was no clock of any kind in the living room area. If I wasn't wearing my watch, I had to run into the bedroom whenever I wanted to see what time it was.COMPLEX - While the complex is attractive, it is spread out and all of our friends and/or relatives were in different buildings (apparently they couldn't put us all in one building). Room keys are also building entrance keys for each particular building. Therefore, anyone visiting us from another building could not get into our building without one of us physically going to the front door of our building to let them in. That can be a pain after a while, especially when you're in a suite where everyone is gathering.SECURITY - Although they try to make a big deal about security, we noticed doors propped open by the staff on quite a few occasions.RECEPTION - While the reception was, in general, wonderful, I was told that the guests at two or three tables could barely hear each other talk because the music speakers were so loud.VALUE - I know that several guests went to other (more well-known) hotels on the strip because they got better deals, so I'm guessing that even the &quot;special price&quot; for regular rooms isn't that terrific. We did not check other hotels, since we wanted to stay where our dauther's wedding was being held, though we did ask for, and received, a considerable discount on the advertised price of the 2 bedroom suite. I have no real complaints about the cost.	
