Mar 30 2009 	Very good value	My wife and I stayed here for two nights, and we would definitely return. We had a nice room, very large, with a good size bathroom. True, there was a &quot;kitchen&quot; area with no stove, microwave, dishes, or silverware. There was a small fridge. We had no problems with nightclub noise at all, even though we were in the exact same location as a previous poster who did. We both slept well. The pool area is pleasant to look at, and gets good sun, but the pool itself is curvy (i.e., not good for lap swimming.) There is a hot tub next to the pool. What we liked most about this place is it was not crowded at all. We were on a bottom floor, with no elevator to wait for. Walking to the casino, coffee shop, or restaurant took one minute. Also, you do not have to walk through the casino to get to your room (as is the case with almost every strip hotel.) We found the staff very helpful and friendly. The poker room manager was especially nice, calling us by our first names by the end of our short stay. The main disadvantage to this place is the location. It takes about ten minutes to walk to the nearest Strip hotel (Bally's). If you want to walk up and down the Strip, you need to take this into account. Twice we decided to get a cab, and both times we had wait times of less than five minutes.We paid $85 for two nights. This was a special rate through Expedia.	
