Mar 23 2009 	Yuck. Just bad just plain bad.	I stayed at the Tuscany Suites at the end of February for a business conference. The rooms are quite large, the pool view is somewhat lovely, and those are about the only 2 good things I can say about my stay. I paid an additional $30 per night for a patio, which is listed as &quot;pool view&quot; I don't like the closed in feeling of hotel rooms, so the patio was worth it to me. What I didn't know is that the 'pool view' is also directly across from the bar with live music that plays until the wee hours of the morning. Perhaps being kept up far later than I wanted would have been palatable if I didn't have to evacuate my room due to a 4am fire alarm. Not that I got much sleep anyway. The pillows are as large and comfy as footballs. They do not use fitted bottom sheets on their mattresses, rather a flat sheet that is tucked in. I'm not a restless sleeper, but found my legs on bare mattress every night. Yuck. The fan in the bathroom was so loud, that I actually took the cover off and disconnected it. The 'suites' angle, well, what good is a kitchenette if there is not so much as a spoon, a fork, a plate or a bowl? There was also no microwave. So the only thing the kitchenette was good for was storing leftover quesadillas from the mexican restaurant that is on the property. Nothing stellar at the restaurants, but not bad and the portions are huge. The fitness center has no TV or music, so it makes any time on a cardio machine pretty brutal. Also, there are 360 degrees of mirrors, so the grounds crew got their eyes full, watching my bottom and my front wiggle all at the same time, as they gathered in the fitness center before beginning their morning. The location is good is you don't mind walking a bit, which we didn't. It is right behind Bally's and you land right in the center of the strip. We walked everywhere from the hotel and it was not a problem. However, at night, make sure to walk on the same side of the street as the hotel, because we found the other side a little sketchy. I've traveled for business for 14 years, so perhaps I'm a bit spoiled. However, I'm also pretty good a going with the flow, but was absolutely turned off by my stay there. I will never say at the Tuscany Suites again.	
