Mar 11 2009 	Fine by us!	The rooms are spacious, clean, and the grounds are garden style apartment style. We're not the type to spend a lot of money on hotel accomodations. When we travel, our intent is not to stay in the room all day, but to be out and about enjoying the area we're visiting. Because of this we found the Tuscany Suites great.Pros: Clean, quiet, great location, helpful and pleasant staff., large rooms and large bathroom with separate shower, tub, and toilet. The toilet in the bathroom actually has it's own door. So your wife can be in the shower while you stink up the toilet area without disturbing her. :)Cons: The kitchenette is really just a sink, cabinets and a fridge. No stove (no biggie, we don't go on vacation to cook) but we were hoping for at least a microwave to reheat leftovers from a dinner/lunch out. There was also no silverware (plastic or otherwise), no plates etc. Overall we had an enjoyable stay. Here's a tip...They say check-in is at 4PM. But you can actually check-in by 2PM at no charge. Or you can check-in as early as 12 noon for a $12.00 early check-in fee.	
Mar 6 2009 	Hotel was fine probably stay somewhere else next time	I stayed at the Tuscany Suites from Feb 22 to Feb 27, 2009. Check in is quick if you can avoid off-peak check in/out times. If checking in/out during peak times it was not uncommon to see 6-10 people waiting in line. Rooms were very large. Kitchen in the room had a mini frig, sink, and stove. No silverware, pots, pans, or dishes. What is that all about? TV had like 10 channels, (no HBO) but I did not spend a lot of time watching TV anyways. The dining options at the hotel were very good. I had some very good meals at the Catina and the hotel diner. I used the fitness center and the hotel and was suprised that is was pretty well equiped and large. The location is OK. It was a couple of blocks walk to the strip. My bed was very comfortable. I did have issues with noise from the room above me, (kids jumping around for hours at a time). I did some additional checking on prices when I got back home. Prices on the strip hotels have really come down a lot lately. I found a stay at the New York or Paris hotels would have actually been cheaper. I would only stay here again if I was doing a budget trip and it was WAY cheaper then the strip hotels. If not, you are much better off being on the strip at the newer hotels. The walk to the strip is not a big deal but you end up walking so much while you are there it just makes sense to be on the strip. One other thing, they really nickel and dime you on the extras at this hotel. They charge $14 dollars a day for internet use. If you want to use their business center it was $.69 a minute to use their computer. They also charge for all local calls and wanted $25 extra for a late. checkout.	
