Sep 1 2008 	Great Place To Stay	We stayed at the Tuscany for three days in August 2008. We loved this hotel. The restaurants are so good we didn't eat anywhere else. The food was great and very reasonably priced. The casino was much larger than we expected, and lots of fun. The grounds are beautiful and lots of shaded walkways. The rooms are huge, with lots of extras and very clean. The staff, from the check-in desk, casino employees, groundskeepers, restaurants and maids were all friendly and helpful. I almost forgot to mention the lounge, it was really nice too, with great entertainment. I wouldn't stay anywhere else in Las Vegas. It's very close to the strip and the airport is about a 5 minute drive.	
Aug 27 2008	Great Place and Location	I just stayed at Tuscany Suites and Casino last week and really enjoyed my stay. This place may have once been an apartment complex or a timeshare. There were many buildings with walkways (3 stories high with elevators). The room was incredibly enormous and clean and the king bed was extremely comfortable. Our safe and hairdryer were both broken, but maintenance came immediately and replaced both of them. The A/C worked just fine. The bathroom was HUGE and also very clean. There was a large room with a vanity/sink area, separate shower stall and separate bathtub..then another door where the toilet was. Our room was at the end of the hallway.. right near the doorway of the building and also the elevator, but it was still very quiet there even though the hotel was full. We had a fridge and a microwave, which came in handy when we brought home some leftovers from our meals. We were in Building O which was a very short walk to the main pool and casino and main building. What we liked best was the size of the room, comfortable bed, cleanliness and the fact that it was nice and quiet (away from all the hustle and bustle of the strip). It is located right behind Bally's about two blocks down (may be a little bit of a walk for some to get to the strip, but it could be done easily for others). We needed handicap parking, but sometimes those spots were taken some times, and we had to park a little further away from our building, but still not very far. Having a car rental was great because we could go anywhere..and used many of the side streets and back roads to get to the main hotels on the strip..many of which do have a back entrance. We didn't eat there, but we did like Terribles..one block down, which had great deals on their buffets ($4.99 breakfast..$9.99 or 12.99 for dinner). There's also tons of other places to eat on this street (Flamingo Road) and in walking distance to the hotel. Pool area was lovely and also very quiet and met up with some nice poeple. There were plenty of towels and lounge chairs..and also plenty of palm trees with shade if the sun was too much (temps were 103 degrees). Also, we booked via their website and received great deal for under $50/night plus tax. We couldn't figure out what all the negativity on this place was about.. Lovely hotel and grounds...we had no complaints at all and would stay there again.	
