Aug 18 2008 	Great Family Stay	Just got back from our trip to Las Vegas, staying Sunday thru Thursday at the Tuscany Suites. We booked through tripres.com. Not sure I'd use them again. Would probably go right through hotel. The hotel puts a $60- deposit on each room on your credit card for incidentals, etc. We did get it all back later. This hotel is located on Flamingo Rd about 1- 1/2 blocks from the strip.Tuscany is an all Suites hotel. But when you book, make sure and tell them exactly what you want. If you want a king size bed, or two doubles. Also specify if you need a microwave/cook top or not. I believe each room comes with a coffee maker and small refrigerator though. We had two double suites. I wanted a kind and a double, but apparently they are not located near one another, so I settled for doubles. I was told by (tripres) that 6 people could fit into suite. This is only correct if you get a king suite with a pull out couch and order for an additional fee a roll away. Roll-aways are not allowed in rooms that have 2 beds per NV law (?)Check in/out was rather quick as the desk has several agents working. Your room key gets you into the buildings and the pool area. Towels are provided. The rooms were both clean and contained 2 double beds, small breakfast table, refrigerator, sink, coffee maker. The toilet is separate from the rest of the bathroom. The bathroom has stand up shower. Soaking tub. (nothing fancy, just a normal tub by itself. ) Nice size sink and vanity combo. Suite is somewhere around 500 sq feet. We were in bldg D the closest to strip. Parking was a breeze and not far to walk from your vehicle unlike many Las Vegas hotels. The pool was any easy walk and by the way was open until 10pm. I have been told that most LV hotel pools are only open until 7pm. You can only enter from Flamingo Rd, so do not try and get in from the street behind as you will be able to squeeze in between fence if you are walking. There is a nice little casino here as well as 3 restaurants. We signed up for the players club. We spent very little honestly, but were able to get most of it back in either restaurant or gift shop comps! The kids ate pizza from the pizza restaurant. They weren't impressed, but I think it was more of a thin Italian style pizza than what they were used to.Check out is btwn 11am-12 unless prior arrangements are made. We ended up getting stuck at a time share presentation, but had left our teen age kids the credit card and all keys. Sadly, they had to wait over 2 hrs in the lobby, but were able to check out with no problems.This hotel is the perfect location for checking out all sorts of locations around the town. Caesars and the Flamingo are within 10 minutes. There is both a AM /PM and 7/11 right around the block. Another sleeper of a casino just a little further up Flamingo is Terrible 's Casino. Sign up for their players card. It's a good deal! Had both the breakfast and dinner buffets there. Not bad at all.General tips about travel here. Bring bottled water. The hottest it got was 121 deg. It was 90deg at 0700. Stopped at a shop in Cesar's for bottled water (2 water +1 Gatorade= $14.50) NO I did not pay such a price. Went to McDonald's and got one there. You can also buy from the locals for $1 bottle. Fremont area gift shops you can get for up to 3 for a buck! Don't try and see everything in one day/night. Space it out. Most of the strip hotels you can park in the valet parking and just tip a couple/few dollars. So much easier than 'self parking'! Wish we would have tried this sooner in the trip!Time shares: We did two. first one got 6 tickets to the Secret Garden and $20 match play at Tropicana. Not bad. Second place got $200. Was quite a bit longer than the first and more of a hard sell. Everywhere you see free info on tours, discounted tours, etc, read timeshare! This is fine if you have the time and either could possibly be interested in timeshares or just want the gifts. Haggle with them for better stuff. And when they say it's just a few blocks away, just laugh. They will all be way down past the airport, &quot;which will some day be the center of the strip&quot;!Ate at several buffets, but might be worth reviewing separately!	
