Jul 1 2008	Good for a Conference	I stayed at the Tuscany Suites and Casino for a conference and was quite satisfied. I was in building E which was a little walk to the main building but manageable, even with a heavy suitcase. The room was large, the A/C unit was loud, and frig was VERY cold. The bathroom was clean and roomy with good shower water pressure. The conference rooms were nice with classroom seating, water in the back, and moderate room temperatures. The women's bathroom was usually crowded, mainly due to an odd arrangement of sinks and towel dispensers. We had continental breakfast (bagels, muffins, and breads) and lunch both days (one day cold sandwiches and salads, and the next day pasta and salads). Everything was tasty and temperature appropriate. Service was efficient and pleasant.The walk to the strip wasn't bad but on my shuttle ride back to the airport I saw several good looking restaurants in the opposite direction (away from the strip). These were within walking distance too and might be a nice alternative. Overall I had a good experience and even won $50 in the casino.	
