Jun 24 2008 	Has been better	having previously stayed at the tuscany I knew what to expect. It is a good off strip location, relatively quiet at night with little disturbance from traffic or passing noise. It is set in relaxing supposedly tuscan vegetation.This trip I was pleased to see both pools cleaned every day as on previous trips both the pools and hot tubs had been grubby. However, the music by the pool was very monotonous. Every day the same CD comprising the beach boys, Kentucky woman and other such classics was churned out hour after hour. Security was slack which for an off strip venue which allows public access to the room blocks was unacceptable. On arrival our block N front door was unsecured. The door handle wasnt working and was jammed in the down position disengaging the locking mechanism. I reported this to security who assured me a mechanic would look at the lock. This same complaint was made at least 3 times during my stay and nothing was done. In addition my room door was almost impossible to open and lock and I returned to my room once to find the maid has not closed the door properly. the hotel didnt see this as a problem!The fixtures in the room, taps in the bath and kitchen were loose and the TV wouldnt turn off. Again these were reported to the hotel who did nothing about these problems. I have reported these problems to the casino and have yet to receive even an acknowledgement of their failings. I doubt if I could be persuaded to stay again.	
