May 19 2008 	Not impressed	I stayed at the Tuscany for my company's annual sales meeting, and if I had a choice I would not stay here again. While the pricing appears to be reasonable, and my first impression wasn't so bad, that didn't last very long. The lobby area smelled of mildew and water damage, the food in the restaurant (Tuscan Gardens) was below average(two members of my group had to return their overcooked steaks), the a/c unit in my suite was miniscule and did nothing to cool the room, the layout of the property was confusing and too spread out, and the distance to the strip was a little too far to walk and through a questionable neighborhood. The conference rooms were laid out nicely (we used one large room and 4 adjacent small ones), however they seemed to be on the same air vent system as the casino, and the smoky air was drawn into the conference rooms all day. The bright side through all of this were the people... the front desk clerks were friendly and helpful, the doormen outside were quick to assist, the catering staff were great and the gentleman who helped us set up our meeting was great.	
