Jan 25 2008	Good price for 15 min. walk to strip.	I stayed at Tuscany for three nights because this was the hotel selected for a work conference. I stayed one additional night at my own expense at fairly low rate. Nice property and meeting rooms. Supply of light refreshments was appreciated at conference. My one room service food delivery took about 40 minutes, but the manager delivered my food himself and explained about staffing issues. Beds and furniture in my room seemed dated, circa 1978. TV had about 10 channels. Huge bathroom with shower and separate tub. Concierge was helpful, but price was incorrect for sedan she arranged - about $5 more than what I was told. Walking to the strip took longer than I had expected, but if you walk in almost the opposite direction, you can get to Hard Rock and the Haufbrau House for excellent beer and German food - worth the 20 minute walk. Overall pleasant experience for work conference, but if I were vacationing in Las Veags, I would probably stay on the strip. This is a good place for someone who does not want to be in the center of all the action and wants to spend less on a hotel.	
