Jan 19 2008 	Even Steven	I stayed at The Tuscany for work during the week of January 16th. This hotel is a good 20 minute walk from the Strip. At night, you might look over your shoulder during the walk as parts of Flamingo are quiet. If you want to see Vegas and want to save money, then this is the place for you. If you want to be in the midst of the Vegas action, then it's not.The hotel is outdated despite a recent renovation. The casino is old fashioned and depressing. After walking though at least 10 others on the strip, this one was sad. There were many senior citizens parked at the slots, a few businessmen there for work, and that was about it. The sportsbook is just two guys behind a counter with a white board.The food was above average. The &quot;basic breakfast&quot; at the cafe is adequate. It costs $4.99 but it doesn't include coffee ($1.50). They give you a 2 for 1 coupon when you check in. The Mexican restaurant got good comments from my co-workers.The rooms are old fashioned but big and include a kitchen so you can save money and eat in. The TV only had 7 or 8 channels. They also charge $10 for early check in. Internet access is an absurd $14.99 a day.If you want a hotel in Vegas to save some money, drop your bags, and hit the town, then this is acceptable if you don't mind the long walk. If you want a hotel to relax in, then look elsewhere.	
