Dec 30 2007 	Great Time and Value	This place is terrific. I had a wonderful time with my husband, we weren't far from the strip, so it was fun taking a (Cold) evening stroll to the Flamingo and Bellagio and seeing some sites. We ate at Marilyn's Cafe, our breakfast waiter, Eddie, (ask for him!) was the best, the food was okay, but you got a lot for your money. For the money spent, we got quite a deal, including a quiet room (we couldn't hear our neighbors), a &quot;mom-and-pop&quot; type operation with good homespun customer service and a genuine smile on almost all the employees' faces. Don't miss the place, you'll love it.	
