Oct 23 2007 	Liked the Tuscany	This is an unusual hotel about 1/2 mile from the Strip. For us, this was a positive, as you are well removed from all the crush, yet only a short walk away. If you can't walk 1/2 mile, you won't be able to handle Vegas very well--lots of walking involved, as traffic is bad everywhere, and driving on the Strip?? &quot;Forgetaboutit&quot; We had very little wait to check in/out and dealt with 4-5 different clerks over the course of our stay, who were all polite and helpful. It was unusual in that it consisted of 6-8 seperate buildings, of 3 floors each. Grounds and pool were well kept, and security appeared to be on the ball (patrolled parking lots in golf carts). Our room was huge, maybe 5-600 sq. ft., but more like an efficiency apartment-one big room, except for the bathroom, which had seperate tub and shower and comode. Room was clean and well furnished. Many reviewers noted that rooms had 2 identical paintings- I didn't notice, as I don't dwell on the artwork in my hotel room when I'm on vacation. To those of you who do, my advice is to get a life. Another plus was the parking, which was near all of the buildings. No waiting, tipping and hassles with valets. For you bargain seekers, the Tuscany is right around the corner from Ellis Island, and their famous $ 4.99 steak dinner, which is better than you'd think. There was some floor noise from the room above us, but it wasn't bad, as this is not a hotel that attracts the late-night party crowd. On-site Mexican restuarant was, good, not great. My wife did complain about the odor (cleaning fluid?), but it didn't bother me.	
