Oct 5 2007 	Great off strip property	Stayed at the Tuscany for two weeks from 19th Sept. We chose this hotel due to the lower prices than the Strip and because we were staying 2 weeks, and reviews being quite positive. We arrived mid afternoon and check in was swift. We stayed in block L which is a couple of minutes walk to reception. The room was large and clean and we received numerous fresh towels per day. They are upgrading the rooms as we had a new sofa and chair. We seen sofa's being removed from other blocks by the dozen. During our stay the pool was closed for two days without much explanation. As a result the lap pool was overcrowded and no sun beds for us to use. We went to the Platinum Hotel next door and asked if we could use their pool, which they kindly agreed to. What a difference to see a beautiful chic pool area with a seriously heated pool which was both indoors and outdoors and the most comfortable sun beds. Anyway back to the Tuscany. The pool area was OK with small towels provided: sun beds easily available at all times of the day although busier at weekends. The pool bar has been closed down and I seen people measuring the pool area which is due to be refurbished. We had no complaints about the hotel or the restaurants. There is one bar with live music in the evening (same every night), but the female clientèle at the weekends is somewhat questionable. Please note that the prices at the bars in the Tuscany were almost half the price of bars on the Strip, except if you are gambling then the drinks are free. We only walked to the Strip once as we had just missed the bus and would not recommend the walk as we felt safety was an issue late at night. We bought a 30 day unlimited pass for the CAT/Deuce buses for 40 dollars at the Moneytree on E Flamingo Road which meant that we did not have to buy a daily pass at 5 dollars. We used the concierge at the hotel 3 times and found them to be informative and helpful. On our last day when we went to shower before leaving there was no water. We contacted reception who said there had been an emergency and they had to shut off the water. They phoned back within 2 minutes and offered us another room in another block and a member of staff brought the key to us within 5 minutes. Overall we had a fantastic holiday and there are unlimited things to do in Vegas even for 2 weeks. I would recommend the Tuscany for the budget minded traveler who is prepared to stay off the Strip which is a few minutes on the bus compared to others on the South Strip which would take a long time on the Deuce to the main part of the Strip.	
