Sep 17 2007 	Good Value. Standard Rooms	I stayed at Tuscany Sept 7 &amp; 8 2007. The Hotel is nice and the rooms are good.The complex is laid out in approx 10 appartment style blocks. My room was in block H at the rear of the complex, about a 2 minute walk through the car park.The rooms are large with cooking facilities, coffee maker, &amp; fridge. Fridge was useful for storing drinks which can be brought to the pool. There is a store within 5 mins walk.Pool area is very nice with lots of beds, towels are provided.The restaurants are great. Italian was especially good, large portions, use the 30% off copon you are given at check in for even better value. Meal for 2 was $20.The cafe in the casino had a great selection &amp; massive portions, also cheap prices.The casino seemed good however I did not gamble here.DownsideNot as classy as hotels on strip, which is a good 20-25 min walk, contrary to other reports saying 10mins.Air con in my room was very noisy and could not be turned off.Overall a good stay and good value. Im glad I stayed here as opposed to Stratosphere or Circus Circus which came recommended, they are miles away from all the action.	
Sep 14 2007 	Great value for a suite alternative to hotel rooms	We loved the Tuscany. The rooms are so huge! Because we were meeting up with family, we wanted space to sit and chat, share a coffee and so on, without people having to stand or sit on the hotel bed. And the Tuscany was trumps for this - sofa, comfy chair, and 3 dining chairs. Plus plenty of room to spread out the suitcases rather than unpack fully.The wee kitchen was useful, mainly the coffee pot and (particularly) the fridge. One coffee filter per day, the pot would make four cups, but only one creamer supplied? Odd.Bathroom is large. The bath appears to only be a half-size, but this didn't bother me because at least it didn't have an over-bath shower - there was a separate shower cubicle. Toiletries nice but no brand names.Outside, we could park right by the entrance door to our block, which was down the back of the complex - but previous vacationers had carved a nice dirt path thru to Flamingo so exiting on foot was quick, 10 minutes walk to Ballys/Bills corner. The main pool was busy mid-afternoon, the lap pool was empty. Fitness room looked good (didn't use it); laundry room was unused and cheap (dollar each time).No problems with reception staff, always courteous. And no problem with housekeeping (daily tip), they always left the extra coffee &amp; soaps that we requested.If you are happy to consider staying off-strip, then I'd recommend the Tuscany. And we'll definitely be going back.	
