Aug 31 2007 	I'd stay here again	I chose Tuscany Suites because I got a great deal through Expedia - about $40 per night - and we don't mind being off the strip. My husband and I stayed for 3 nights and we'd stay here again. The upsides: The room was cheap, yet clean, large, quiet, and comfortable. The bathroom was nicely designed (very large with tub and separate shower). The restaurants were good and affordable - my husband especially liked the Mexican. The gift shop is open all hours and was very handy for forgotten toothpaste, magazines, booze, souvenirs, etc. The pool and hottub were very clean, plenty of chairs, radio music playing, open long hours (7am-10pm) and hardly any children at this time of year, thankfully. We purchased beers/coolers at a local mart (2 blocks away), kept them cold in our fridge, and brought them down to the pool area in a bag with ice. We walked to and from the closest strip hotels (3 long blocks) - to Caesar's, Flamingo, Bally's, Bellagio. We walked to and from NY, NY and MGM but I wouldn't recommend this to everyone (about 2 miles). Lawry's Steak house is across the street. Tuscany is fairly close to the Hard Rock Hotel (about 3 blocks), which has great casino/lounge/nightclub/rock memorabilia/Nobu restaurant to check out. The Planet Hollywood buffet (Spice Market Buffet) is killer and highly recommended (voted best buffet for 2007).Cab fares to Treasure Island, Wynn: $8, Fremont St. (downtown): $15, Premium outlet mall (downtown): $17. The downsides: slow check-in, no shuttle to the strip so you must be able to trek fair distances. I would have liked a room with a balcony or patio - I suggest you request this if you'd like.	
