vice also.Tuscany Gardens, the Italian place near the front of the lobby ,was also excellent and excellent service. also good amount of food and well prepared. I would highly recommend it whether you stay at the resort or not. we did not try the &quot;Cantina&quot;, so cannot comment on that one. also use the coupons you get on check in...they cut the price of meals 10 to 30%, depending on the coupon. The Bar near the Slots was awful. although wonderful bartender, talkative and fun, the drinks tasted like nothing more than water. I had a margarita and it was just water....there was no flavor at all. we did not use the other bars or night club across from the restuarant so can't remark on that either. All in all, I would stay there again, but not in summer when kids are out of school and likely to be vacationing there with mom and dad. We don't go to Vegas to be surrounded with kids.	
Jul 22 2007 	nice place to stay	this was my first time booking a place to stay that was not on the strip. I was pleasantly surprise with the room. I did book the place with i4vegas.com in which I payed about $55/per night but I had book the reservation about 3 weeks in advance. I did notice that the closer to my actual arrival date the price was almost reduce by half. The walk to the STRIP took my husband and I 15 minutes which was not too bad considering we would be walking anyway. The room was a nice size and really enjoyed the separate toilet from the shower and vanity area. The casino was a nice size considering the hotel. I did 2 loads of clothes while we were there and the price was about $1 each plus drying. All in all in was an very inexpensive place to stay that was not a dump.	
Jul 19 2007 	Great Experience	We stayed at the Tuscany at the beginning of July. I was not disappointed. It's close enough to the strip and perfect if you have a vehicle to get to places and still park nice and close to where your room is. The rooms are huge and look exactly how the hotel website portrays them. The room was clean and the maids kept it that way. We were in building C and although it says there are cooktops in the room, ours had been taken out (fine by me as we had young children with us) we did have the fridge, sink, table etc. My only real complaint with the room is the sheets on the bed. They really should use a fitted sheet on the bottom instead of a flat one. We found it really quiet and peaceful as long as you stayed out of the main building or the pool area which is where you want it to have action. The landscaping was so beautiful. We especially enjoyed the pool area. We didn't eat at any of the hotel's restaurants but I did visit the gift shop for snacks and it was nice that it was open late. I played some of the slots in the casino and more than doubled my money so that was a plus too. As for check in and check out, it was slow because only 2 people were handling the desk and one of them was a trainee...they could use more people at the desk in my opinion. All in all we had a great stay and we will definately stay there again.	
