Jul 8 2007 	Great Vacation at the Tuscany	My husband and I stayed at the Tuscany last week July 1-7. We read the reviews and were excited. The room (king) was HUGE as everyone says. They cleaned our room every day, vaccumed the entire bit. I am kind of a clean freak, so I am always somewhat leary when we stay in hotels. Our room always smelled fresh (not cover up sprays) and was very clean.Last time I was in Las Vegas (10 years ago) I stayed at New York, New York ( It had just been built). It was nice but like most people say, the wait to check in is long and you usually have to walk far from the elevators in the large hotels. With the Tuscany being smaller and more spread out, eveything is close. Plus, the landscaping is nice when you are walking the winding paths to get to your destinations.You also do not have to pay for the work-out room, where at the larger hotels it is around $20.00 for a day pass. We ate at Marylin's Cafe and The Cantina, they were both really good and very inexpensive. My husband got the cod fish and two sides for $8.00.The Tuscany is more of a family atmosphere than the larger hotels due to the kitchen so singles or couples might take that into consideration. You really do not notice the family atmosphere unless you are at the pool. We are a young newly married couple and it did not bother us (just noted).The staff was really nice and friendly. What you get for the price, you can not beat this place. We were in Vegas when the Temp. was at record highs (116 degrees) about 13 degrees higher than normal. We rented a car and it was the best thing we could have done. You can see more of the strip and parking is free all over the strip. We are really glad we stayed at the Tuscany!	
Jul 7 2007 	Large suites	My husband and I recently stayed at the Tuscany for our 20th wedding anniversary trip to Vegas. We chose the Tuscany because of the central location and larger sized rooms. The grounds were very well kept and our room was HUGE...plus extremely clean. I'm a very light sleeper so upon check- in... I asked for a room that was located in a quiet section of the resort. Honestly....we never heard a &quot;peep&quot; the 4 nights we stayed in the room. The Tuscany is just 2 long blocks behind the Bally's Resort on the strip...which takes about 10 minutes to walk. If you buy the deuce bus ticket it also covers the #202 line going East and West in front of the Tuscany...so we walked out front to the bus stop then over to the strip. Don't make the same mistake we made by thinking the bus going East somehow turns around and then goes West. If you're going West to the strip you need to leave the Tuscany...cross the street and get on that bus #202 going west to the strip. In other words...each bus is like a one way going in the direction you want to go. The Tuscany has a nice pool and we had an amazing Italian dinner at the nicer restaurant by the front lobby. We enjoyed the clean casino, too. I watched the travel clubs and I got our room for $56.00 a night....what a bargain!!!! If we go back to Vegas...we would stay at the Tuscany without a doubt!	
Jul 7 2007 	Great stay for the money	RoomThe Tuscany is an all suites hotel, converted from apartments. As a result the rooms have consistent style and are equipped with 2-ring hob, fridge/freezer, sink, coffee machine. However, crockery, cooking utensils etc are not supplied - if you wish to use the kitchenette, bring your own!Large comfortable and clean king bed, with 2 sofas and coffee table in addition to a dining table. More than big enough for two adults! Air-conditioning appears to be an after thought with a wall attached A/C unit. Although very effective, ours was very noisy - it's a fairly consistent drone, so its easy enough to sleep through overnight.Maids cleaned rooms daily making beds, replacing towels etc and arrived at a reasonable time which was nice so we weren't disturbed early!BathroomBath, separate shower, separate toilet were all spotless and modern. Shower was hot when required. Large bathroom with large wall mirror. Again, noisy extraction fans, but no big deal as they only come on when you turn the lights on.Location2 blocks from the strip. Safe 10 minute walk to/from strip along busy Flamingo road. No shade makes for a hot walk during the day. StaffI get the impression that staff are friendly and approachable for &quot;run of the mill&quot; enquiries, however when asking for advice and help over and above normal duties, I encountered attitude. Not a problem as long as you stick to your guns. The concierge will help you with attractions and bookings for shows etc. We enquired about a Grand Canyon helicopter flight. My advice is use them for the information, but book direct with the company rather than through the hotel, we saved $70 on our trip.FacilitiesPool large, good jaccuzi. Clean towels are provided. They seem to leave the radio on all day, which can be annoying if you are right by the speaker! Very clean and plenty of sun loungers and space. Even at &quot;93%&quot; occupancy, the pool was never busy. Seem to have good facilities for conferences, meetings and weddings. RestaurantsMexican restaurant looks good on paper, but is disappointing. Not recommended. The Tuscany Gardens Italian has a good atmosphere, food is good with good service. Use the 30% off voucher they offer on arrival and the price becomes reasonable also. Cafe does a good breakfast 24/7, with quick and friendly service. It seemed popular with gamers and guests alike. CasinoWe didn't visit for the casino and had no intention of gambling. Smells slightly smoky, although the whole hotel is now non smoking (apart from the bar), it was clear it wasn't always that way.OverallCheaper, good value off-the strip hotel. For first time in Vegas we were happy with our stay. Nice to be away from the strip to get some peace and quiet - the hotel is nice and quiet.	
Jun 20 2007 	Perfect!	We stayed at Tuscany with about 30 of our friends and family due to my wedding being held at the Tuscany Chapel on April 28, 2007. We hadsuch a great stay. It is so quiet and relaxing, but yet we were able to have our fun as well. The slots in the casino seemed pretty loose,a lot of us won some money there. I loved the restaurant Tuscany Gardens where we held our reception dinner, the service was great and the food was phenomenal. The strip was a little ways away, but wedidn't mind walking it - it sure was good excercise. Oh and the size of the rooms - they are the size of a small apartment. I had such a fabulous time, I will definitely stay there again!	
Jun 17 2007 	Perfect for Us-Comfortable 	If you are looking for a place that is exciting with lots of action, then this is not the place for you. However, if you want a comfortable room in a quiet area with nice grounds and pool, and a low-key casino, but is within walking distance to the action and good restaurants, then this just might be right for you.We knew we didn't want to be constantly surrounded by people and the noise of the strip, so after reading the reviews on this site we chose the Tuscany Suites. We found it was perfect for what we wanted. We could walk to the strip (about 1/2 mile, but get a taxi if you don't want to walk in the heat) and if we didn't want to eat in one of the restaurants in the complex (there were 3), we could walk across the street to Lawry's, McCormick &amp; Schmicks, or Gordon Biersch (?); go around the corner to Ellis Island for their excellent BBQ joint; or walk a block to an old-school Italian restaurant. We arrived at 1:30 and were told checking in early would require an additional $10 fee, so we elected to wait until 3:00. The desk clerk graciously offered to pre-check us in and assign us a room and we could return at 2:30 for the keys. In the meantime we drove about a mile east to an Albertson's market and stocked up on groceries.Our room was on the 3rd floor of building C, away from the main street. It overlooked the building next door but that was OK. As mentioned before, the room was huge with king bed, a dining table, couch, chair, desk, and a small kitchen area with sink and refrigerator (no microwave but someone mentioned in an earlier post that one could be requested but we didn't ask). Our only issue with the room was that the bed was short-sheeted and I found myself remaking it every night (why don't all hotels use fitted sheets??). The bathroom was very large with a tub, separate shower, large vanity area, and the toilet was in a separate room (I loved this). There was also an ironing board and iron in the ample closet.The grounds were very pretty with lush plants and trees and the pool area was relaxing on a warm day with shade under the palm trees, and the large spa was just the right temperature. I especially loved the winding paths as I could take my early morning walks around the grounds without venturing on the street. There is also a fitness center with a lap pool and in the same building is a laundromat, which was handy since we were midtrip and I needed to wash a few things.All in all we were very pleased with this hotel and my husband I agree that we would stay there again when we return to LV.	
