May 29 2007 	Great place to stay	This was my first trip to Vegas, so I don't have other hotels to compare it with. The rooms in this hotel are huge. There were three of us staying there and with us and our luggage, no one was tripping over anyone or anything else. We had two double beds and a sofa bed, with room to spare when it was pulled out. There is also another chair, kitchen table and chairs.We didn't have a microwave in the room at first, but after inquiring about one it was delivered to our room almost immediately. The staff was very friendly and helpful. We made several requests for extra towels and washclothes and they were always timely in bringing them to us. The bathroom is rather large, and everything was clean.The hotel is within walking distance from the strip, but we never walked it. There is a double decker bus (Deuce) that cruises the strip. If you pay $5 for a 24 hour pass you can transfer from the strip bus to the 202 that goes down Flamingo road. That bus lets you off right in front of the Tuscany. You couldn't ask for more convenience. The pass is even good to use on the city buses.You can't beat this hotel for the price. I know people who have visited Vegas and have spent way more for a room, but didn't have what we did. I will be staying there again.	
