Oct 23 2006 	Quiet place practically on the Strip!	This review is for my husband's business trip from Oct 15-19. This his review, not mine.I had a one bedroom suite. It had a king size bed, small sitting area, small dining table, work desk, and a small kitchenette. THERE WAS A COFFEE POT IN THE ROOM. The bathroom had seperate bath tub and stand alone shower. Everything was clean. Air conditioning worked very well. Hot water takes a minute to kick in. No complaints.Over the hotel was very quiet, clean, and relaxing. It is 2 blocks off the strip. The walk to the strip was about 8 minutes. I did not go into the pool, I felt it was too cold but it was open. It looked nice. There were not a lot of children here. The casino was small. I finally learned to play roulette here because of the low minimums. There goes 3 hours of my life. The roulette dealer was quite helpful in explaining the rules of the game to me. If you are new to gambling, definately start out in a smaller casino like this and go early in the morning. I was the only one at the table and gained valuable knowledge from this. Drinks at the casino bar are only $2.50-3.50 so it is really reasonable if you don't want to wait for the waitress to bring you one.Marilynn's Cafe is what I ate for breakfast twice. I got the contential breakfast one morning and some type of standard breakfast with fruit plate. Both were good. Decent price for breakfast in Vegas. The Tuscany Gardens was very pricey. Nice atmosphere, just expensive. I got the chicken fettichini alfredo for $15 and a salad was not even included. Overall I really enjoyed my stay there and would recommend it to others. Its good for romantics/couples. The location is ideal for business travelers who may need to go into Vegas or surrounding cities easily because Flamingo Rd is easily accessible from the interstate/highway.	
Oct 23 2006 	Great Hotel with one minor exception	We stayed at the Tuscany from Oct 19-22. Its a newer hotel with a small casino. It is about 1 1/2 Las Vegas blocks from the strip. The rooms a huge and the cleaning staff friendly. But be prepared for one unexpected expense.Here it is: Hotel check in for the Tuscany is 3pm. If you arrive earlier than that time you can get your room - for a price.The Tuscany charges 10$ for 'early' check in. Even though your room is ready, they still will charge you. Our flight arrived earlier than expected and we land at 1030am. We reluctantly paid the fee and got to our room to freshen up from the long flight. That is the only problem with the hotel. Everything else was great.	
