Oct 14 2006 	Disappointed	I am sitting in room N103 as I write this, very disappointed. This is a very big room. Almost the biggest hotel room I’ve ever been in. The bathroom is also very large with a separate toilet, a tub and a shower. This room also has a kitchenette. The facilities, pool, restaurants, and casino are all very good. Tuscany is very well located, just a couple of blocks away from “The Strip,” on East Flamingo Road.Regretfully, if I come to Las Vegas again, I will look for another hotel. To start with, the door to the toilet room doesn’t close and in fact must be held (with a knee, no less!) against the jam, if you want privacy. There is a large tile missing (6 x 6) on the baseboard. It’s hard to figure how a supposedly good hotel would allow that to just slide. The shower head is placed for midgets but that’s not unusual. The closet sliding door is off its track and although I put it back on to some extent, the problem is that the track is bent and loose making it unserviceable. The ice machines on all three floors of this building were not working when I arrived. Room service offered to send up ice for a charge. Guest services sent a maintenance man and sent me a plastic bag of ice. The first floor (my floor) ice maker is still not working but the second floor machine is, now.The furniture is really cheap to begin with and in my room, it is dirty and stained. I was in a friend’s room and it’s identical except it wasn’t dirty so that I noticed. The TV is a standard 19” with only 12 cable channels, and 2 more for the hotel’s use. It does have pay-for-view, however.The bottom sheets are not fitted, they are flat sheets tucked in. I tend to rate a motel on this. A fitted sheet stays on the bed without shifting better but is more expensive and less versatile to the motel, only being a bottom sheet. This is really sub-par for a hotel of this supposed level.Last night’s dinner in the Tuscany Gardens, the hotels main restaurant was very good. It gets busy so make reservations. This mornings Sunday Brunch Buffet in the Cantina was also very good with an accomplished omelet chef on station. A I said, I am sitting here disgruntled because I wanted a dish sent to my room from Tuscany Gardens but room service will only send food from the snack bar! That menu is exactly that – snacks! As I’ve been typing this, a menu for a pizza place was shoved under my door and they do deliver! How they’ll get into the building without a key is questionable but they got in to shove their menu under the door, didn’t they. Disgruntled has gone to furious! I tried to call the pizza place and I can’t get an outside line. It’s unbelievable. The operator comes on and says she’ll get me an outside line but when I try the local call, I get an error sound – NOT a busy sound. This place is down the street. I call back and tell her but she doesn’t want to listen and hangs up on me! I spoke with the manager at the front desk and she offers to send a repair man to my room. Clearly, the problem isn’t in my room. This is hopeless. I had to go out to my car to get my cell phone (I seldom use it). Of course it’s roaming. I must be fair and admit that having once been a Marine Officer, my voice can be somewhat “forceful.” Still, the issues that brought me to be “forceful” should have never occurred. As I said, it is regretful that I cannot recommend this hotel because it could be a great facility.On a positive note, last night we took in “Folies Bergere” at the Tropicana. This is one of the oldest original shows in Vegas. It was great. Funny thing, a lot of people seemed to be sitting on theirs hands. These performers danced their hearts out. I highly recommend it.	
