Sep 21 2006 	excellent value great stay	We booked it from Vegas for 1 week stay in Aug. Average daily rate is about $80. Our room is in building H (or maybe I) on 1st floor. The room was nice and big, clean. Room service is standard. Separate toilet and bathroom is great since we have small kids and they always wanted to come in when you're there too :-)). We went to the pool almost everyday during our 1 wk stay. The pool is a nice size, plenty of laungers/chairs/tables which is a surprise----I had to tip to get a chair when I stayed at the much higher end Mandalay Bay/The Hotel. Never gambled in the hotel's casino but did take a look there. It's small but not so smokey. Pool side cafe is nice and clean with large tables. Location of the hotel is why it's much cheaper. It's about 2 blocks off the strip. We walked everywhere to the north and south of strip with no problems. Make sure you wear comfortable shoes. We stocked our fridge with beer, water, juice, yogurt, milk ... from the 7-11 store next to the corner gas station. 7-11 store's coffee is much better than the one from the hotel though, and cheaper. For food we ate at Ellis Island for 3 nights--great food at unbelievably low prices. Don't miss their $4.95 steak dinner with soup/salad every night. Their fried fish (cod filet) and fries basket is huge--enough for two for around $6.75. Ellis Island is next to the 7-11 store. these are all within a block. Free parking.For other nights we ate at: the World Buffet at Rio ($27.99/pp. $21/child), good food but a bit over priced. RedHotBlue restaurant at the Mandalay Bay is standard, don't try their baked chicken it's just too bad. Their spaghetti with meatball is excellent for about $15. Make sure you have breakfast at Mandalay's Bayside Buffet at least once--great food, large varieties, quick service, smoked salmon every day ....hmmmmmm yummy.We pretty much used the Tuscany hotel as a base and ventured out during the day, only go back to sleep at Tuscany at night. W