Sep 12 2006 	Our new hotel of choice in Vegas	All the pluses of this property outweighed any disappointments we may have had. Things we liked: Moderate price; a well maintained pool area with warm water and all the towels one could want; a short walk to the pool, casino or anything on the property from our non-smoking first floor unit in &quot;F&quot; with &quot;no search&quot; parking spots right outside the door; easy auto access to Flamingo Road both directions making it very easy to drive to any of the dozen other casinos we visited; very easy access to airport or downtown from Paradise Road, walking distance to Bally's corner; walking distance to Terribles 2 for 1 $5.38 breakfast buffet; friendly poker room with two tournaments daily; late night bargain breakfast at Marilyn's Cafe; fitness center with lap pool; good Mexican food with 2 for one welcome meal; huge suite rooms with table and chairs, microwave, frig, couch, walk-in shower; separate tub, separate stool. Battery was low in the safe and repair was there almost before I got back to the room. Disappointments: Wi-fi is overly expensive at $10 per day, but dial-up is still available at $1 per connection; door lock occasionally stuck and had to be retried; ice machine on our floor was not working (other two floors had ice); phone jack at desk did not work. (We didn't request repair for any of these items before checkout.) Unless you are used to the concierge level of the Wynn or Venetian, you will be well satisfied with the Tuscany. Given availability and competitive prices we wil probably make this our base hotel in Las Vegas from now on.	
