Aug 20 2006	A real gem	I read through the reviews and decided they were complimentary enough to risk booking at the Tuscany Hotel. We needed just one night's stay before continuing on our journey through the Western States, and the Tuscany was one of the few we tried who didn't mind accommodating us on a Saturday night. We stayed in mid-July. Although we arrived very late we were treated courteously and efficiently by the desk clerk. The rooms were easy to find, although parking gave a us a few problems as every other guest had parked up for the night at a much more reasonable time. We went to have a quick look around the casino and it was much larger that I had expected, in fact the whole complex was much more spacious than I could have imagined. The slots were loose and I came away with an advantage, even though I didn't stay long as it was so late. My husband and I rose early and did some further exploring before we left. We decided that if we ever came back to Las Vegas at some time in the future, we would definitely book into the Tuscany Hotel again. The rooms were huge and very comfortable. There was a lovely pool complex and beautiful gardens. It took us 8 minutes to walk from our hotel room to 'back end' of Ballys, so don't be put off by the thought of not being on a hotel on the strip. If the idea of walking is totally abhorrent, a taxi would set you back just a few dollars, and that would be offset by all the money saved by not paying for the over-inflated prices charged by some of the well-known hotels on the strip. I've stayed in those (this was my 10th visit to Las Vegas) and the rooms at the Tuscany are much nicer. Go for it, you will probably return again and again to the Tuscany.	
