Jul 10 2006	Good for the budget traveler but be wary	This hotel is a 2-3 star hotel - a budget hotel with spacious grounds. The rooms are large. The grounds immense. Decorations are simple and the grounds manicured. Though both are showing signs of wear. The resort is just a short walk to the strip - Bally's. For the price, it could be a nice stay for the budget traveler especially those with a family or looking to stay out of the casino/hotels. Free parking close to your room is a plus compared to the distance you have to walk in the large hotels. (As posted earlier - leave your stuff in the car, go check-in, then drive to the parking area near your room.)Our stay was filled with problems. First we were sent to a room that was locked or would not open - right next to the elevator. You could feel the floor rumbling as the elevator moved. We trucked all our stuff back to the lobby (thank goodness we were traveling light) and were told they would send someone up to see why we could not get in - it might take a while. I asked for another room instead of waiting - away from the elevator (I remember reading someone else's review about the noise residing next to the elevator). We were able to get in to our room (not in the same building as before but not near the elevator) but it was not made up. A call to guest services - we could either change rooms again or housekeeping would be sent. We opted for the former - housekeeping was completed within the hour. The rooms are large including the bathroom. It was nice to have a separate shower and tub. There is a kitchenette but no supplies - sort of defeats the purpose of having a stove in the room but the fridge, microwave and coffee pot ( there were no cups other than plastic cups in the bathroom) could be helpful to most travelers. Although neat, the place needs a deep cleaning and maintenance. My feet were black from walking barefoot on the carpet and things like hooks to hang towels were loose. Some of the towels were stained and had hair stuck to them -though you could tell they had been washed. The lampshades kept falling down when we touched the lamps but they were quickly righted - held on with magnets. The TV has very few channels (about 6) so traveling with kids could be a problem. We did have a non-smoking room which really was smoke-free. The walls were thin - you could here surrounding noise but luckily the buildings are small and there is not a lot of traffic in the hall or outside between the buildings. The lobby is smokey since the bar is right night to the entrance and reception desk.We did not use the restaurants, the pool or the gym. The casino was not crowded and we were able to pay a long time on the machines on the initial wagers with little money lost. I cashed out at around my initial wager from boredom after nearly 1/2-1 hour of playing on the same machine (a few times).On checkout my bill contained a charge that we did not make. The rep who initially &quot;helped&quot; me indicated it would take about 20+ minutes to sort out and did I still want to dispute it (and wait). That answer was completely unacceptable to me and I asked to speak with the manager. The supervisor quickly zeroed out my account indicating accounting would pull the receipt to match the signature and sort it out - I did not have to wait. Unknown if this will be a problem - too soon to tell. We will not be staying here again. However for those who want a motel near the strip at a very affordable price for Vegas - this is a good deal with all the budget motels and hotels disappearing - especially such a close walk to the center of the strip. There are many people who have had great vacations here from the reviews and they did address our problem with check-in however they should not have occurred in the first place.	
