Jul 2 2006	good stay for a great price	We just returned from a 6 night stay at the Tuscany and I can say that I would recommend it to those who want to stay “off the strip” for a great price. The room was HUGE! The photos on the home page of this site are accurate of the room’s size.As far as checking in, we arrived on a Sunday afternoon. There was no line or any problems. However, we were given a handicap accessible room. There were no signs on the door, but it had a fold-up seat and hand shower in the tub. It also had a walk-in shower. The toilet was in the open in the bathroom, not in a separate room as described by others. BUT, the room was clean and nice.We were in Building “A” which is the closest to the corner of the property by the roadway. Our walk to the strip took 15 minutes. That was to the corner of Flamingo &amp; L.V. Blvd. It took 11 minutes to get to the rear doors of Bally’s and walk thru their air conditioned casino. Bally’s is also connected to the Paris casino and you can use their a/c to get a little further down the strip.The sidewalk between the Tuscany and Koval is closed due the construction of the Platinum, but there is space to safely walk along the roadway behind the large orange cones. We did it over &amp; over. I missed the bus stop across the street, but there is one between Koval &amp; Bally’s coming back toward the Tuscany.The casino at the Tuscany is not recommended. The waitress service in non-existent. I had to stage a “sit-in” at the roulette table to get a drink. I was the only one there! I told the dealer that I wasn't playing until the waitress came by and brought me a drink. The casino floor manager came over after the dealer called him, and he got a waitress from another station to bring me a drink after I threatened to cash out and go elsewhere.As others have said, don’t miss the Ellis Island Casino next door on Koval. They have their own brewery and their beers are great. I liked the light beer the best; however the amber ale was very good. And, they have their own brewed Root Beer. I know, you didn’t go to Vegas to drink a Root Beer, but it’s good anyway. The waitresses at Ellis Island make a pass about every 5 minutes, so order a light and a root beer! Be sure to tip her! You can belly up to the bar and get the same beers for only $1 anytime. Their steak special (10 oz sirloin $4.95) is really good. We were in town 6 days and ate it 3 times! Get there before 6pm or the wait is very long. We waited 1 hour &amp; 15 mins once, 30 mins, then went for lunch and was seated immediately. I won at their video blackjack machine every time we went there (while waiting &amp; drinking their great beer) and basically ate free! I didn’t try their BBQ, but it sure smelled good and the line was long. Others complained about the service at the Tuscany. I had to get security to come open the safe so that I could use it. It took them about 5 minutes to get to the room from the time I called. We also had a problem with the door entering the bldg. We walked to the front desk and by the time we made it back to the room, security was there resetting the door lock. I have no complaints about their service.My wife is very cold natured. We would at times turn the room a/c off to get the room to warm up. We were on the 1st floor and that may have contributed to that. We would turn it on after she was comfortable and it would cool the room down very fast.We ate the after midnight special at Marilyn’s. The waitress wasn’t a happy camper and was fairly grumpy. She walked up to the table and sarcastically said “I guess you want the special”. The food was ok. We got a 6oz steak, 2 eggs &amp; hash browns for $2.99.We didn’t make it to the workout room (HA!) so I didn’t see the lap pool. We did go to the outside pool one day and it was nice. The “hot tub” next to it had powerful jets and the water was hot. We did not eat at any of the other restaurants at the Tuscany, nor did we go to the bar, so I can't comment on them.I would probably return to the Tuscany if I go back to Vegas. It was a good stay for a great price.Mark S.Baton Rouge, LA	
