May 22 2006	Great value	Stayed at the Tuscany Suites for a week (30th April) with a group of 13.It was ideal for our group as the hotel is small compared to most in Vegas which meant that it was easy for us to meet up and bump into each other.For those on a budget its a great choice, unlike most hotels you don't have to go through the Casino to get to your room which is a definite plus. 10 min alk to the strip.The rooms are large, clean and comfortable - our wardrobe doors were broke but we didn't bother to report it, rooms which are nearest the road can be noisy - especially if you are trying to catch up on sleep!Theres a small but attractive pool and Marilyns cafe was a godsend - open 24hrs and reasonably priced.Concierge was very helpful when booking Grand Canyon trips and got us a good discount.Grand Canyon is a must - we were recommended a company called Maverick - we were told safety is high on their list so we decided to go with them - you can get cheaper but it was worth the extra money.We went for the trip that lands in the canyon then brings you back over the strip at sunset fabulous!!!!Another great venue is the Voodoo lounge 51 floors up 0 an open air club on top of the Rio Hotel well worth a visit!If you want to blow the budget book a table at The Mix at Mandalay Bay - ask for a table outside and be there for sunset - amazing food, service and venue(but not cheap - about $120 each)	
May 21 2006	Would stay again	Just spent 4 nights at the Tuscany. Big room with a fridge and microwave &amp; stove There are no utensils or cutlery in the room so come prepared. Stayed in N block which is right at the back of the complex. Top floor room got very warm and airconditioner was too noisy to have on while sleeping. That for me was the only negative. There is a 7/11 around the corner, a grocery store down the block and Ellis Island casino next door does a great steak deal for $4.95 that is not on the menu.. just ask. I didnt try any of the restaurants at Tuscany. The walk to the block is no big deal. Its one block to the back of Ballys, to either walk through the casino in the airconditioning to the strip or to catch the Monorail. To me it felt the same distance as walking to my room from the front desk. The latest I walked back from the strip was 10pm but there were alot of people around and I felt safe. Front desk helpful and there is Internet access on site in the business centre although it may be cheaper to go to a Internet cafe it was handy to have there. It was nice to get away from the masses of people on the strip. The hotel hosts alot of meetings and conventions. Would stay there again next time I am in Vegas.	
May 15 2006	Nice hotel near the strip	I needed an inexpensive hotel room near the strip and Tuscany Suites proved to be an excellent choice. The resort is only a few years old and the rooms are huge. I would classify Tuscany Suites as a high class budget property. There are about 10 buildings within the complex, each three floors, looks similar to a nice condo complex. For those with a car, you can park near your room without having to walk through the casino. The room I stayed in had a small fridge, microwave, sink, and grill. The only drawback to Tuscany Suites is that the walls are rather thin. If you are a light sleeper you might want to sleep on the top floor. And its too far to walk from Tuscany to the strip during the hot summer months. But overall, if you don't need to be on the strip at one of the megaresorts, Tuscany Suites is an excellent alternative.	
