Apr 4 2006	Nice hotel terrible service	We stayed at the Tuscany as part of a large group. Upon arrival at around 7PM we were told that we had no reservation. After supplying a valid confirmation number I was told that their computers crashed the day I made the reservation and they had no record of it. They did give us a room at the group rate we had been promised, but when I made the original reservation I requested two double beds because we had four people staying. The room they gave us was a king room and had a single bed. This is when the problems started. My wife called the front desk, was told that rooms are on a first come first served basis and there were no double rooms left. Although we had reserved two double beds we had not previously been &quot;assigned&quot; a room and therefore could not have a double room. They say this is standard practice; however others in our group that came after us were given double bed rooms. My wife then requested to talk to the night manager and was transferred to his voicemail. She hung up, called the front desk again and was greeted by the same employee who was laughing and carrying on a separate conversation. She explained that she was trying to contact the night manager and had just been transferred to his voicemail. The employee laughed and told her that the manager was right there and gave the phone to him. After some pressure the night manager said he would send us a rollaway bed. We complained that one rollaway would still leave one of our daughters to sleep on the floor. After he refused to do anything else for us and hung up I walked to the front desk (we were in one of the remote buildings, it was a long walk) to talk to the manager face to face. He then told us he'd be sending a &quot;full size rollaway&quot; but could not send two; it would be against fire code. When the rollaway arrived it was a twin size bed. When I called the front desk to complain they refused to answer the phone, I left it ringing for 10 minutes and no answer. I called from my cell phone, one ring to an operator, two rings to the front desk. Apparently they didn't care to talk to us. I was told that another bed would be sent immediately and would be in our room in 15 minutes. By this time it was after 8:30PM and my children were hungry. We waited 25 minutes then went to dinner. Upon returning from dinner around 10PM we found no bed had been delivered. Again I called the front desk, no answer. I walked to the front desk and was told that the bed was requested and would be requested again. At 10:30PM we received the second bed (and apparently violated fire code for the rest of our stay). The morning we checked out I voiced my concerns to the person checking us out; she didn't seem to care and told me to fill out a comment card. She would not give me information regarding the hotel owner/operator, only the name of the front desk manager and a flyer with the address where I should send the comment card. This is a nice hotel, big spacious rooms, nice facilities and the Mexican restaurant has good food and an excellent staff. It's unfortunate that the employees at the hotel do not care to help their guests and go out of their way to cause problems. I thought for sure the day staff would be concerned at the behavior of their night staff but they seemed to think it was business as usual. In a place like Vegas where there are so many places to stay you'd think service would be important to them but apparently it's not.	
