Nov 28 2005	Don't bother with the Tuscany Cantina	On Thanksgiving Day we ate at the Cantina at the Tuscany on Flamingo Road. The food was so-so, but the service was horrible. There were only a few customers in the restaurant yet the service was very slow and unfriendly. No one smiled or greeted us. It was like we were an unwelcome interruption. We had to wait a long time to be seated, for drink service, delivery of the meal, and refills. We had to go ask for additional services such as refills, more chips, etc. On the positive side the appetizer bean dip and salsa were delicious as was the fried ice cream. The food was hot when served but nothing to write home about (tacos, flautas, enchiladas, chile rellenos, rice, beans, burritos, etc.). All in all we were disappointed in the Cantina and do not recommend it to others.	
