Nov 16 2005 	Good not very "Vegas" but Good	I stayed at Tuscany for the SEMA show held earlier this month. For those who have never been, The Tuscany is a very clean, manageable, hotel that is situated on a property with a 'main' building that features registration and a bar / restaurant area, and several straight-line two-story guestroom buildings that are efficient albeit not very spectacular. The advantage with this lay-out is not having a ten mile walk from your room to the lobby as is the case in most Vegas properties. The Tuscany features clean and spacious rooms and one can still smell fresh paint and new carpeting. There is a lot to like about the Tuscany. I have stayed there before and probably would stay there again, but . . .What I DISLIKE about The Tuscany: At no point during your stay will you feel like you are in Las Vegas!! The Tuscany is as boring as it is efficient. Aside from the army barrack-styled guest buildings, Tuscany features the most unimaginitive casino I have ever been to outside of an Indian reservation. It is really like a rectangular white-walled gymnasium that has been carpeted and filled with slot machines. Tuscany does not - however - force you to walk across the casino floor to get to your room: a Vegas first for me. When my friend 'Vegas' Jenny from San Luis Obispo, CA told me she'd never heard of it, I knew I was in trouble. When you stay at Tuscany you might even forget you are in Vegas. When I was there, it felt like being at a Golf resort in Tampa or Palm Springs. A little escapism from Vegas can be a good thing after a few days though. There was one creepy thing that happened to me during my stay: I walked out of the shower in my room to see a brown roach-looking bug looking back up at me, but . . . I do not blame the hotel. There is little doubt of their cleanliness and one should not forget Vegas is in a desert! Besides, I felt bad for the bug - after seeing me naked, seeing any other nude male guests will just be a disappointment. Bottom line: I recommend the Tuscany as a BASE, but your Vegas fun will be had elsewhere.	
Nov 15 2005	UK VISITOR TO TUSCANY	My Husband and I stayed here from 24th Oct for 7 nights. We were looking for a place between a motel and strip hotel that we had stayed in before. This was a great find. Great location even without a car 7 min walk to strip well lit at night. Very peaceful setting, nice pool area. The staff were very nice and dealt with our request for a change of room with balcony in a very efficent manner. The rooms were a great size and bathroom was bliss ( even if bath was low to get in and out of) The kitchen area was a added bonus with fridge and coffee maker, lacked utencils.The Italian restauran was very good,service,food and price was well worth a visit as was breakfast buffet. The only down was the building works going on next door for 24 hours and this was a factor when trying to sleep.But I would recommend this to readers of the review and my friends	
Nov 3 2005	Still a great place to stay	Stayed at Tuscany Oct 28 - Nov 1 and it was just as great as our first stay there two years ago. My only complaint is that they wouldn't match a price I found on ---- so I wasn't able to book directly through the hotel. We arrived very early in the a.m. our first day and after breakfast in the cafe we were able to check in at 9am. Service a the front desk was great. Rooms are HUGE and well-kept, bathrooms have seperate toilet &quot;room&quot; so sharing a bathroom with 5 other people was never a problem. We had six in our group (dont' tell the hotel) and never felt cramped. The only downside for some may be that the rooms with two beds have double beds instead of queens. Having a kitchenette with storage space is a huge plus! There is a small mini-mart across the street for snacks and beer. We had a rental car so we drove five minutes down Flamingo to a grocery store for food and beverage. A 5-10 minute walk will get you to the center strip or the monorail station at Ballys to explore elsewhere. Access to the hotel is really easy from east or westbound flamingo, parking is right outside your building and getting to the airport takes about 10 minutes unless you are in heavy traffic. Casino is small but does have all the table games with low minimum bets, plenty of cheap slots, video poker, and a poker room. The tables are generally very slow except for weekend nights and the dealers are helpful for new players. Join the players club for some good deals and to get some cash back for your play in the casino. I highly reccomend the $1.99 late night breakfast special in the cafe. Can't say much about the food in the other restaurants as we only ate a the cafe, but it is certainly not too pricey. Pool area is not huge but very nice with small tiki bar. I can see it getting crowded in the hot summer months but we never go then so can't say for sure. Fitness facilities and another small pool are also available for use with no fee. The layout of the buildings is a bit sprawling but I like that they are only three stories tall so you are never forced to wait for an elevator. The buildings farthest from Flamingo and the pool area are quietest, but the closer you are to Flamingo Road, the quicker the walk to the strip. They are building some condos next door right now but we were never bothered by construction noise. The Tuscany is a great value for people who want to have a large suite room in a quieter place without tons of people everywhere and don't mind a 10 minute walk to the strip. I highly reccomend it!	
Oct 18 2005	Fantastic Oasis of calm close to the Action	Guiided as always by the other reviews we were delighted with the room so large for us Europeans with Coffee maker and fridge though no other cooking facilities but we had no plans to cook in a City full of cheap eats. The location was fine for us only a few minutes walk from Ballys and either a monorail from there up or down the strip or walk through to Paris my favourite the Buffet amazing value. Ellis Casino just around the corner more old Las Vegas as was Freemont Street a Must do at night. The rooms were well maintained and the pool area lovely quiet relaxing and a good pool service . We ate in the hotel a few times breakfast buffet good value though no doubt better options on the strip. Good parking facilities and supermarkets close by for water and soda. Cannot understand how anyone can complain about this hotel for the price that you pay. The strip is an experience and yes some of the hotels amazing but some so large and impersonal with so many non guests trawling the corridors!! The Tuscany provided us with access to the strip in minutes in an ideal central position so could do either end of the strip in a day but more importantly for us it provided us with a relaxing holiday too as we could escape the crowds and the noise and swim sunbathe or snooze . For the price we got on Expedia October less than £60 a night a real bargain. Hired a car and found driving around easy and allowed direct access to Hover Dam at our pace a great sight and other odd trips out to Henderson Boulder City and Galleria shopping Mall and others and Golf .	
