Jun 19 2005	Comfy quiet 	Just gotten back from staying at the Tuscany. We had a large double bedroom on the first floor in block C, which is right next to the main hotel area and not too far from the road. What we liked about this hotel was that you could get to your room without having to go through the lobby or casino everytime. In fact, the Casino is off to the side of the lobby so you could have easily avoided it altogether if you were not into gambling. We made use of our fridge and kitchen area by going to the local 7/11 and buying up supplies. The walk to the strip is about 10 mins and we did not find this hard going at all. We used the monorail a lot to get ourselves up and down the strip. We went in through the back of Ballys via the Race and Sports Book and the monorail entrance is just around the corner. Our room was large and very comfy and clean. We had no problems whatsoever. There is construction work going on next door (but there's construction going on all over Vegas) but we were not bothered by this.We did not use the restaurants or pool so cannot comment on those.This hotel is ideal if you want a nice comfy large room, with fridge. Don't mind a short walk to the Strip and want peace away from the action and the bling bling of slot machines but near enough if you want it.	
Jun 14 2005	Nice but stay now because it will fall down soon	HUGE room with full kitchen--range, microwave and half-refrigerator--no oven. But they're not into upkeep. It's a property made up of several three-story buildings with nice landscaping in between. It's only three years old and there were several things that should have been fixed in the room that weren't. When we mentioned the loose shower head and the backspash separating from the wall, the front desk wasn't really interested. It's not on the strip, but in the morning or evening, it's not a bad walk--about two long blocks. In the heat of a summer day, you'll want to take a cab--and they're expensive. The casino is boring and smoke-filled, but since we didn't go to Vegas to gamble, it wasn't a big problem for us. There were ants in our kitchen--just one or two every morning--and since we were on the third floor, we assume there are ants all over that building. We got our room for $50 a night through Travelocity and it was definitely the best deal of the whole trip. Oh, did I mention the rooms are gigantic?One caveat--there is construction going on next door. Don't let them put you in building A on the construction side. They start working as early as 3:45 AM, but most mornings around 5:00.	
