Nov 16 2004	Pleasant surprise!	We just returned from our trip to Vegas, after staying at the Tuscany from November 10 – 14, 2004. We had NO problems with either the staff or the room. The room was BIG, with a kitchenette, sofa, dining area, etc. Not many channels on the cable, though. But our room on the third floor of building M was mostly quiet, except for the occasional noisy guests in the hallway. And it appeared to have been cleaned every day, including fresh towels when we didn’t ask for them.We spent some time at the pool and jacuzzi, which were never crowded, the food at the Tuscany Gardens restaurant was VERY GOOD, and the service in both the hotel and restaurant were VERY GOOD.Antonio the concierge was very helpful in booking a Dam tour for us, and pointing out restaurants and free shows. He even called us about our camcorder, which we had left in his office.15 minutes to the Strip on busy, well-lit Flamingo Road – we walked it at night and never worried about our safety. Overall, a great stay. We’d stay there again, however, the next time we’re in Vegas we’ll probably stay at another hotel just to stay at someplace different.	
