Sep 29 2004	Little Italy in the desert	We have just returned from a great 2 weeks at the Tuscany Hotel. When reading some reviews we were a little apprehensive about whether we had made the right decision...we did. The Tuscany was a breath of fresh air in a 100+degree desert.Are you looking for a friendly, quiet (not in your face like other large hotels),very large and clean rooms, low rise buildings in a beautiful palm tree setting and a swimming pool that you can actually sit around without being bombarded by screaming teens and also being provided with plenty shade if the sun becomes too much for you?If the above is for you then Tuscany is your ideal location.The Tuscany is only a 5 minute walk from the strip, (1 1/2 blocks for all you Americans), on a well lit main road and gives you the chance to experience all the bright lights but with a good nights sleep at the end of a busy day.This is our 3rd visit to Las Vegas where before we stayed at Bally's and Monte Carlo and although both hotels were excellent the Tuscany definately had the edge for us. You are away from the biz...you meet people from all over the world and because the hotel ambiance is peaceful and friendly people take the time to talk.Service at reception was friendly and the bell porters could not have been more helpful...maid service was second to none with towels and bedding changed daily....the 24 hour security of this hotel was obvious and the guards (both women &amp; men) were friendly and for anyone (young or elderly) who like a nice walk in the evening without going to the strip the Tuscany's 2 1/2 acres makes a lovely night stroll and gives plenty of photo opportunities.	
