Aug 21 2004	Tuscany suites -- good value for money	We stayed here in two groups in August 2004 and were very pleased with the Tuscany. We have stayed in various hotels in Las Vegas over the years and I think this is certainly as good as any in the same price range. The hotel is perhaps half a mile off of the strip on Flamingo and sits in its own small grounds, which makes a pleasant change from high rise blocks. The rooms are very large and in one of our parties we had a couple of children in the same room, so having a lot of extra space with a setee &amp; armchair was very good. The rooms also have refrigerators &amp; some have microwaves &amp; cookers (no utensils we noticed though). The pool area was grassed and good sized considering the number of guests, the pool was very clean and nice and the area was kept clean. We stayed at the Excalibur a few years back and the pool area was invariably littered, overcrowded and quite dirty - so this was a nice change. We were also checked in quickly and I never once saw people being held up at reception, which is again a bit of novelty in Vegas where we have before now had to wait more than an hour to check in. You get what you pay for and yes I think there might have been an odd niggling problem like a wardrobe door falling off but it was fixed quickly and it was overall value for money....	
