Mar 17 2004	Great for conventions	I come to Vegas every year and stay about two weeks setting up and working at a convention. Tuscany is my favorite for doing a trade show. First of all, the rates are excellent. Secondly, it's quiet and away from the strip and you don't have to walk a mile through the casino to get to your room. Third, the rooms are huge and comfortable, and there's plenty of room to spread out and do work. You will want a car when you stay here because, like all the hotels off the strip, cabs do not come by often (and cabs in Vegas are expensive! You'll save money in the long run renting a car). The hotel is about a year old, and as long as they keep the rooms in top shape, I'll stay here. When you're in town for two weeks, the casinos get old really fast. Tuscany is different, and much nicer.	
