Jan 30 2004	Suite Experience	My family and I stayed at the Tuscany Hotel and Casino (January 23-25). We checked in after 7pm and had our room within 10 minutes. The hotel rooms are located away from the casino. We stayed in building &quot;B&quot; which was located right in front of Flamingo Avenue. We intended on making the trip an adult only thing, but the kids (ages 5 and 6) came along anyway. The room was CLEAN, LARGE, and COMFORTABLE. It totally felt like a suite. The bathroom had a tub and a shower. The room had a &quot;sitting area&quot; with a couch and a chair. We also had a &quot;dining area&quot; with a round table and 4 chairs. There even was a mini-frige, microwave, and stove. So, if you're planning a trip with kids this is the PERFECT place. We plan on staying here again whether the kids come along or not. You can walk to Bally's (it's not a far walk) and take the monorail to other casinos. Tuscany's casino isn't the biggest, but plenty of people looked like they were having fun. As for the serivce, many big resorts don't have to rely on being polite in order to get people to come back. I never encountered 1 rude person during our stay. I felt as if we were treated like they wanted us to come back on our next visit to Las Vegas. We've stayed at Monte Carlo, Luxor, Aladdin, and New York-New York. Tuscany is a great deal for a great room. E-mail me if you've got any questions.	
