Dec 11 2003	A great place to stay	We were very impressed with the Tuscany after staying at many of the on-strip and off-strip properties in Las Vegas. The rooms are large, clean, and well equiped. There is a very nice pool and hot tub. The exercise room is spacious and well equiped with modern machines. There is also a lap pool and hot tub seperate from the main pool. The casino is nice and well ventillated. It has a lot of video poker machines with good pay scales ( 10-7 double bonus, full pay dueces.) There is also a good selection of the &quot;penny machines&quot; which my wife loves to play. The bar tenders are friendly and efficient. Service by the cocktail waitresses seemed quite slow, but they were all friendly and quite personable. I was a little disappointed in the casual dress of the employees. It was difficult to tell who was an employee and who was a customer. However the bikini clad blackjack dealers at the Monday Night Football Party was a nice touch. We were very comfortable, and would definitely stay there again.	
Dec 9 2003	More like a mile to the strip	Well, where do I start? The only really good thing to say about the hotel is that the rooms are huge and clean. We requested a crib before we arrived and there were none available upon check-in. We were promised one &quot;first thing in the morning&quot; and we had to call twice to ask for one and finally got a crib at 8:00 the next night. It is over a mile to the strip and they must contract out with a specific cab company because we never waited less than 45 minutes for a cab from the hotel. There weren't enough pool chairs to accomodate the guests. At least 20 people had to put towels down on the ground and around 5:00 the sprinklers came on soaking everyone. I would definitely spend the extra money to stay on the strip next time and avoid all the hassle.	
Nov 26 2003	Excellent	This place was much more then I expected. The room was very large, clean, quiet, and comfortable. Small cooking area, table and chairs, couch and chair. I'm not a gambler but for anyone that is, the casino is small. The food was decent, no complaints there, good price too. If you don't mind being two long blocks from the strip. This is a great place to stay. Check in and out was quick and pain free. I would definitly stay here again and will recommend this to friends. For the price this place was excellent.	
Nov 11 2003	Great new hotel fabulously large for 4	Wonderful new hotel 2 (long city) blocks from the strip. Very clean suite-style rooms with plenty enough space for 4 people. Staff were friendly and prompt enough. Grounds are well-kept and well-manicured, nice pool area, decor is quaint Tuscan. Try the Palazzo restaurant inside the hotel if you love Italian. All dishes we had were superb, unusual for Vegas/Casino/Hotel fare. Room prices were quite reasonable, especially with a convention in town (when DOESN'T Las Vegas have a convention?). Will book with them again.	
Nov 11 2003	Superb Location Superb deal	I stayed in Vegas for two nights and just booked it off the net not really knowing where i was staying. I was very lucky because this hotel is only a ten minute walk from the centre of the strip which meant that my blisters were smaller than they could of been! The hotel is really clean and tidy and the rooms are huge. Check in was quick which is more than can be said for the airport terminal like queues in some of the strip hotels. The casino is a nice size, the food good and reasonably priced. If you don't mind not being in one of the big ones, then this is the place to stay.	
Nov 5 2003	really enjoyed tuscany hotel	We just got back from Las Vegas where we stayed at the Tuscany Hotel. Our room was very big and clean. We had a view of a garden walkway and the next building. Which was ok. It was very quiet and the staff was nice. We didn't care for the casino though. The dealers were not friendly and so we walked over to the Flamingo and had a great time there. It is easy walking to different hotels and the cab's are always available if you want to go farther and it didn't cost that much to get around town. The door men were very helpful and friendly. The food in the cafe was very good. We didn't try the nicer restaurant. I loved their prime rib sandwich. And the cafe is open 24 hours. I would recommend this hotel to others. Oh, and plenty of towels and hot water. Room service is slow and they didn't bring everything I had asked for. But overall I would give the Tuscany a high score.	
Oct 29 2003	Not too bad!	You can't beat the price! We paid under $60.00 for our room which was clean, spacious, and in excellent working order. Upon arrival, the front desk errored (saying they had only a room available for 3 of the 4 nights we booked), however they did overcome that obstacle. It is located a good hike from the strip, especially if you've been on your feet all day. We were able to take a bike taxi to the Tuscany from the strip. The pool and lobby are beautiful. If you don't compare to the super hotels on the strip, this is quite a nice hotel.	
Oct 18 2003	Enjoyed our stay	Stayed at the Tuscany June 2003. Enjoyed it so much we returned in September. The room was spacious and very clean. Never a wait for breakfast or lunch. Reasonably priced menu for dinner. My type of casino....not loud or congested...We will be back.	
Oct 15 2003	summer nightmare	Billing department is messed up, Any promotions needs to be check, otherwise they will be misleading.During Summer, They had ants, crawling on top of their kitchen counters, I called several times for maintanance but no luck, It took 6 hrs. before they can fix the problem. Still after a spray, Ants came back.Who would want to stay and sleep with ants, Not safe if you have children.I stayed recently August of 2003. When I complained with the manager, They can't help it, it is summer......	
Oct 13 2003	Great Room for the Price	I visited Tuscany with 2 friends over Labor Day weekend (2003). We are in grad school and were looking for a nice room on a budget (non-Strip prices during the holiday weekend). A friend had previously stayed at Tuscany and liked the room. Our room was basically a suite, though without any dividing wall--and fit the 3 of us perfectly. The bathroom was nice and had a separate shower and large tub, plus a huge full-length mirror that was helpful when we were getting dressed to go out. The closet was a bit small but we were only there for the weekend so we managed to make it work. We enjoyed the main restaurant, great service and good food. Our room was relatively quiet but then again we weren't in it all that often. The only downside? Because Tuscany is off the Strip there was sometimes a long wait to get a cab (they aren't just idling in front of the hotel). Plus, it's major cab fare to get to the clubs on the Strip. All in all though, Tuscany was great for the price.	
Sep 7 2003	Pity about the Fire Alarm	A good, new, clean, multicultural second division hotel located just off the main drag. Rooms are large - like a suite without the wall. Pleasant staff, nice buffet breakfast.Our trip was spoiled by someone setting of the fire alarm deliberately - at 3.45 am. Alarm did not stop for 45 minutes. Not the hotel's fault I suppose, except their security staff seemed slow to respond, but no appologies offered - no free meal - or free night offered to make up for a ruined day, due to lack of sleep, following the disturbance.Arrived at hotel at 11.am and they would not let us in until 3pm - because they said the room was occupied - we found out later that it was not -as the room was so hot at 3pm that we could not cool it down in time for a compfortable night (outside temp was over 100 when we arrived)Probably would not stay there again, but if you have a booking here already and are looking for guidance - I would probbly not cancel - try it for yourself	
